# Experiment No.3:

The aim is to implement the concept of an **abstract class** in Java by defining a class that contains abstract 
methods and concrete methods to demonstrate inheritance.

A. Write a program to implement the concept of abstract class. 
B. Create an abstract class Base with two integer variables and a method getdata(int a, int b) to assign 
values. 

abstract class Shape {
	abstract void draw();
}

class Circle extends Shape {
	void draw() {
		System.out.println("Drawing circle");
	}
}

class Main {
	public static void main(String[] args) {
		Shape s = new Circle();
		s.draw();
	}
}


// abstract class Shape {
